<h2>What is Astronomy?</h2>
<p>
Astronomy is a natural science that studies celestial objects such as planets,
stars, galaxies, black holes, and the universe itself. It explains their origin,
evolution, and behavior using physics, chemistry, and mathematics.
</p>
